"{\"uid\": \"independent.co.uk-sport-olympics-anne-hidalgo-e-coli-paris-b2587523.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Notifications can be managed in browser preferences.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 52, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in  Swipe for next article  Removed from bookmarks  I would like to be emailed about offers, events and updates from The Independent.\", \"from\": 54, \"to\": 321, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Read ourPrivacy notice  Swimming training for the triathlon was cancelled for the second day in a row because of concerns over water quality but organisers remain confident Tuesday's men's race will go ahead as scheduled.\", \"from\": 322, \"to\": 543, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 346, \"end\": 354, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Swimming\", \"score\": 0.9997847180532647, \"rank\": 0.0002028577890514877, \"text\": \"Swimming\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Swimming\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Swimming\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Heavy rain can lead to increased levels of the harmful bacteriaE.coliin the Seine despite more than a billion euros spent on cleaning up the river in preparation for the Games.\", \"from\": 545, \"to\": 721, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The deluge that affected Friday's opening ceremony and continued into Saturday has had an effect, with the athletes again prevented from going into the water for the scheduled familiarisation session on Monday morning.\", \"from\": 723, \"to\": 941, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Organisers released a virtually identical statement to Sunday, saying: \\\"Paris2024 and World Triathlon reiterates that the priority is the health of the athletes.\", \"from\": 943, \"to\": 1104, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The tests carried out in the Seine yesterday revealed water quality levels that in the view of the international federation, World Triathlon, did not provide sufficient guarantees to allow the event to be held.\", \"from\": 1106, \"to\": 1317, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1136, \"end\": 1141, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999998876612671, \"rank\": 1.0961701165259444e-07, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 1232, \"end\": 1247, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Triathlon\", \"score\": 0.9999999999979536, \"rank\": 2.0885408554228063e-12, \"text\": \"World Triathlon\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Triathlon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Triathlon\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This is due to rain that has fallen on Paris on 26 and 27 July and the impact it had on the Seine river.\", \"from\": 1319, \"to\": 1424, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1359, \"end\": 1364, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999998779003, \"rank\": 1.2220286842508303e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1412, \"end\": 1417, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999998876612671, \"rank\": 1.0961701165259444e-07, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Given the weather forecast for the next 36 hours, Paris 2024 and World Triathlon are confident that water quality will return to below limits before the start of the triathlon competitions on July 30.\", \"from\": 1426, \"to\": 1627, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1477, \"end\": 1487, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.5437911953151735e-19, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1492, \"end\": 1507, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Triathlon\", \"score\": 0.9999999999979536, \"rank\": 2.0885408554228063e-12, \"text\": \"World Triathlon\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Triathlon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Triathlon\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As observed in July, with summer conditions, water quality in the Seine has improved significantly.\\\"\", \"from\": 1628, \"to\": 1728, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1694, \"end\": 1699, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999998876612671, \"rank\": 1.0961701165259444e-07, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris 2024 president Tony Estanguet, Paris mayorAnne Hidalgoand Marc Guillaume, the top government official for the Paris region, all took a dip on July 17 to showcase the Seine's improved cleanliness ahead of scheduled open water events in the river.\", \"from\": 1730, \"to\": 1981, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1730, \"end\": 1740, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.5437911953151735e-19, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1751, \"end\": 1765, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tony Estanguet\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\"}, {\"begi